        "comment": {
            "name": "comment",
            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/13638",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=gavin",
                        "name": "gavin",
                        "displayName": "Gavin",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Zend_Session could be modified to throw an exception when the specified save_path is not writable.\n\nA lot of people like to set \"ini\" settings in .htaccess.  We could skip the is_writable check, if save_path was not set using Zend_Session::setOptions().  However, ignoring this group of people would allowing warnings for bogus save_path's set in either php.ini or .htaccess.  Alternatively, a new \"no_save_path_test\" option could be added to Zend_Session::setOptions(), thus providing a way for developers to explicitly disable the test, if they are not using files for saving their sessions, *and* do not want to set a valid value for \"save_path\".  This latter option is not currently planned, since we are not investing extra effort for extreme edge cases yet (pre ZF 1.0).  However, in principle, I do not see a problem with adding this option.\n\nA totally different perspective:  We should not check their PHP ini settings at all in ZF core components .. This is the job for Zend_Environment, which should be executed everytime they change their environment or application configuration settings.\n(10:23:18 AM) cleanfunnyjoke: I could go to either of these 2 extreme perspectives .. they both appeal to me.  For high performance situations, I would lean towards using Zend_Environment from a cron job and avoiding the overhead of per-request checks\/tests. However, we are not yet at ZF 2.x, Zend_Environment is in incubator, etc. and we want to avoid premature optimizations.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=gavin",
                        "name": "gavin",
                        "displayName": "Gavin",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2007-03-22T13:16:49.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2007-03-22T13:16:49.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/13648",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=gavin",
                        "name": "gavin",
                        "displayName": "Gavin",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "See FishEye link above for more information on the change committed.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=gavin",
                        "name": "gavin",
                        "displayName": "Gavin",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2007-03-22T18:46:06.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2007-03-22T18:46:06.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/13694",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=shahar",
                        "name": "shahar",
                        "displayName": "Shahar Evron",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Sorry for reopening, but fix in r. 4193 is not very good. I use a special session save handler (Zend's Session Clustering mod_cluster) which does not care about the value of session.save_path - so I have no problems starting sessions regardless of the value of this directive, but now I can't use Zend_Session anymore.\n\nIn fact - looking at phpinfo() shows I have no value for session.save_path so I am not sure the check is even valid (what is the default if there is no value?)\n\nIMHO we should not try to \"rape\" the PHP environment by performing our own checks. PHP is *ment* to show a warning when your session save path is not usable and I don't think we should override that. ",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=shahar",
                        "name": "shahar",
                        "displayName": "Shahar Evron",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2007-03-24T15:08:03.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2007-03-24T15:08:03.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/13695",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=gavin",
                        "name": "gavin",
                        "displayName": "Gavin",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Hi Shahar.  We discussed this specific issue during the last devteam meeting and decided that the few people who are not using the default file-based session handler will simply have to fix save_path by giving it a valid value, even though they might not need a valid save_path.  Some other options were discussed (noted above), but ruled out for now.\n\nWhy not set save_path to a valid value?\n\nAllowing PHP to emit warnings for invalid save_path is contrary to our coding standards:\nhttp:\/\/framework.zend.com\/wiki\/x\/PQ",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=gavin",
                        "name": "gavin",
                        "displayName": "Gavin",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2007-03-24T22:37:55.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2007-03-24T22:37:55.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/13698",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=shahar",
                        "name": "shahar",
                        "displayName": "Shahar Evron",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I see - if the issue was already discussed I see no point in opening it again - although I am not sure it's our job to override warnings emmitted by the PHP engine (not by wrong code in a ZF class). \n\nI will set my session.save_path to something just to override these warnings.\n\nI think this should be documented though.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=shahar",
                        "name": "shahar",
                        "displayName": "Shahar Evron",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2007-03-25T09:23:21.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2007-03-25T09:23:21.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/13712",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=gavin",
                        "name": "gavin",
                        "displayName": "Gavin",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Reopening issue in order to be able to close it properly and remove the \"not an issue\" resolution.\n\nFixes were applied (see FishEye link for information).",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=gavin",
                        "name": "gavin",
                        "displayName": "Gavin",
